id: pmc-09bu
title: Isolate package-install integration tests from the user's pm home
description: "The package activation smoke test only redirected PM_GLOBAL_PATH, leaving HOME and XDG state shared with the operator. A real install test must be hermetic so it cannot read or mutate personal/global pm configuration."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[4]: hermetic,package-install,privacy,test
created_at: "2026-07-10T23:01:30.633Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-13T22:53:53.876Z"
deadline: "2026-07-11T23:01:30.633Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-13T22:42:19.161Z"
author: codex
estimated_minutes: 45
acceptance_criteria: "The package-install smoke test pins a temporary PM_PATH and PM_GLOBAL_PATH, uses isolated HOME/XDG/user-profile roots, and does not inherit npm lifecycle or credential-bearing environment state; The activation/generate/check assertions pass when /tmp is already a pm workspace and INIT_CWD points at the source checkout; The full release gate passes against the repository-locked latest pm CLI SDK"
definition_of_ready: Current origin/main is checked out; latest pm CLI dependency is installed; no unrelated working-tree changes exist.
reviewer: greptile
risk: low
confidence: high
sprint: 2026-07-production
release: next
reporter: codex
severity: medium
environment: "Node 22.19.0, npm 11.17.0, @unbrained/pm-cli 2026.7.13; /tmp contains an ancestor .agents/pm tracker and npm INIT_CWD points to the source checkout"
repro_steps: "Run NPM_CONFIG_USERCONFIG=/dev/null npm run release:check while /tmp/.agents/pm exists; before the fix, the package-install fixture discovers the ancestor tracker and package doctor reports unrelated extension collisions."
resolution: Pinned project PM_PATH and global PM_GLOBAL_PATH to the temporary fixture; replaced process.env spreading with an operating-system/network allowlist so npm lifecycle metadata and registry credentials cannot reach child pm commands; updated the locked pm CLI to 2026.7.13.
expected_result: "The package-install integration test cannot discover ancestor/operator pm context or inherit npm lifecycle/credential state, and the complete release gate passes."
actual_result: "134 tests passed, including real package install/doctor/generate/check flows; typecheck and build passed; npm audit found 0 vulnerabilities; npm pack dry-run passed; pm-changelog reported CHANGELOG.md current."
affected_version: 2026.7.13
fixed_version: next
component: test/generator.test.ts
regression: true
customer_impact: Prevents tests and review bots from coupling to or modifying private user configuration.
dependencies[1]{id,kind,created_at,author,source_kind}:
  pmc-3j77,related,"2026-07-10T23:01:30.633Z",codex,null
comments[5]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-10T23:01:30.633Z",codex,Discovered while manually running the full release gate against real local pm data.
  "2026-07-10T23:05:34.344Z",codex,"Greptile P2 accepted: spreading process.env could preserve an operator-exported PM_GLOBAL_PATH. The test now overrides PM_GLOBAL_PATH to a temporary path in addition to HOME and XDG directories."
  "2026-07-13T22:32:20.661Z",codex-root,"Regression reproduced on 2026-07-14: npm run release:check sets INIT_CWD to the source repository. The integration test spreads process.env into child pm commands,so pm resolves the source workspace instead of the temporary workspace,loads unrelated extensions,emits collision warnings,and creates .agents/pm/extensions in the source tree. A control probe with INIT_CWD unset reports zero warnings; the same probe with INIT_CWD set reproduces all eight warnings."
  "2026-07-13T22:35:15.245Z",codex-root,"Root-cause correction after a controlled second probe: INIT_CWD was a real inherited context hazard,but the immediate collision source was ancestor workspace discovery. /tmp already contains a pm tracker,so pm init in /tmp/pm-changelog-install-* reused /tmp/.agents/pm and loaded its ten project extensions. Pinning PM_PATH to the test directory removes all eight warnings. The child environment remains allowlisted so INIT_CWD,npm lifecycle metadata,and registry tokens cannot leak into the integration process."
  "2026-07-13T22:53:53.869Z",codex-root,"Pre-push Greptile review 9b6f4fa2-f517-4e9e-9186-c334f7a3f50b P2 accepted: the original allowlist assertions were invariants but did not prove sanitization of hostile input. The regression now injects inherited INIT_CWD, PM_PATH, PM_GLOBAL_PATH, and NODE_AUTH_TOKEN sentinels, then proves lifecycle/credential values are removed and pm roots are replaced. Full release gate remains green: 134/134 tests and 0 production vulnerabilities."
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-10T23:01:30.633Z",codex,Use temporary HOME and XDG roots rather than only PM_GLOBAL_PATH because package lifecycle state spans standard user directories.
learnings[3]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-10T23:01:30.633Z",codex,Package integration tests must isolate both product-specific globals and standard HOME/XDG locations to avoid privacy leaks and nondeterminism.
  "2026-07-10T23:05:34.577Z",codex,"When constructing a hermetic child environment, overriding HOME/XDG is insufficient if product-specific path variables can be inherited; explicitly replace every supported storage-root override after spreading process.env."
  "2026-07-13T22:35:15.245Z",codex-root,"Hermetic pm integration tests must isolate both axes of context: PM_GLOBAL_PATH for global package state and PM_PATH for the project tracker. HOME/XDG isolation alone does not prevent nearest-ancestor workspace discovery in shared temporary directories."
files[3]{path,scope,note}:
  package-lock.json,project,Locked pm CLI dependency graph
  package.json,project,Latest pm CLI development dependency
  test/generator.test.ts,project,Hermetic package installation integration test
tests[2]:
  - command: "NPM_CONFIG_USERCONFIG=/dev/null npm run release:check"
    scope: project
    timeout_seconds: 180
    pm_context_mode: tracker
    note: Full release gate with isolated npm user config
  - command: npm test
    path: test/generator.test.ts
    scope: project
    timeout_seconds: 120
    pm_context_mode: tracker
docs[1]{path,scope,note}:
  README.md,project,Package installation behavior reference
close_reason: Hermetic PM_PATH and PM_GLOBAL_PATH isolation plus an allowlisted child environment eliminate ancestor/operator context leakage; the latest-CLI full release gate passes all 134 tests.
body: "## Context\\n\\nProject management is context management. Integration tests must prove package activation without consuming unrelated operator context.\\n\\n## Scope\\n\\nIsolate the package lifecycle smoke test and verify the full release contract."
